The visualization should be simple, yet it should help users understand the basic structure and design of a tree. The user must be able to interact with the visualization in the following ways: 1. A button to toggle the display of leaves on the tree. 2. A dropdown menu to change the color of the tree trunk. 3. A slider input to adjust the number of branches on the tree. 4. A checkbox to enable or disable the animation of the tree swaying in the wind. Ensure that the final output includes index.html, styles.css, and script.js files.
Note:
- The visualization should be implemented in JavaScript with HTML and CSS.
- Ensure that the output has both index.js and index.html files
